[2] Pakistan
Date: 8 or 15 Nov 2006? (See below)
From: Joseph Dudley <jdudley@eaicorp.com>
Source: The International News [edited]
<http://www.thenews.com.pk/update_detail.asp?id=12502>

Karachi: 101 VHF suspect patients flock to various hospitals
-----------------------------------------------
Patients with suspect Viral Hemorrhagic Fever continued to flock to
different hospitals across the city, and 101 patients have been admitted
due to their condition on Tuesday [7 or 14 Nov 2006? The original report
was received by ProMED on 8 Nov 2006, but the URL above gives a date of 15
Nov 2006].
Dr. Shakil, Incharge - Dengue Control Center, told media this evening that
10 new admissions of suspected Viral Hemorrhagic Fever were also reported
at Civil Hospital, Hyderabad on Tuesday [7 or 14 Nov 2006?]. "The number of
confirmed dengue cases has come to 1080 in Sindh, including 1064 in Karachi
only," he said.
The new admissions on Tuesday [7 or 14 Nov 2006?] were said to be besides
299 already hospitalized in Karachi and 22 in other parts of the province,
bringing the total number of suspected VHF cases to 2935 across Sindh,
including 2888 in Karachi only and 47 in interior areas during last few months.
"It was again on Tuesday [7 or 14 Nov 2006?] that 91 VHF/Dengue patents
were released from different hospitals of Karachi and 2 from Hyderabad and
one from Mirpurkhas," he said.
Dr. Shakil, to a question, said VHF/Dengue induced deaths come to 29 in
Karachi and 4 in other parts of the province since June this year [2006].
--
Joseph P. Dudley, Ph.D.
Chief Scientist,EAI Corporation
